name: Starbucks
directions: By the entrance, to the right of the counter/merchandise
comment: Open to public, no purchase required

name: Wheaton Community Center
directions: Second floor to the left

name: Moapa Town Library
directions: Behind the librarian's desk on the right
comment: The library is also a designated National Safe Place.

name: Truro Brewing Company
directions: Back left corner.
comment: This queer owned business is very welcoming and I loved their honey brown. You can probably use the restroom without purchase.

name: Hidden MN
comment: Roseville city statutes require listing male and female bathrooms. However, this is an inclusive business and people are welcome and encouraged to use any bathroom they feel fits their needs.

name: Magic Gardens
directions: In the rear indoor gallery space.
comment: Inside an area only accessible to paid guests.

name: Karen Bellitto
directions: At start of tour in Eastern State Penitentiary museum
comment: Inside museum grounds. Paid entrance required.

name: Tel Aviv University Gender Neutral Bathroom
directions: First floor of the Social Work building, opposite room 152
comment: Available for both students and staff members at the university.

name: Brink of the Lower Falls (Parking Area)
Brink of the Upper Falls Parking Area
SUNY Brockport Hartwell Hall
directions: One on each floor

name: Varsity KBS Facilities
comment: Available to all job applicants and employees.

name: Florida Atlantic University - Schmidt Family Complex
directions: Building under parking garage, next to FAU Stadium. Enter Schmidt Complex closest to stadium and make a left. Gender neutral restrooms (2) are on left.

name: The Play Cafe
directions: Straight in from the front door, first door on the right just behind the play market.
comment: There is no sign saying for customers only.  And the owner also supplies some diapers and feminine products!

name: Noodles and Company
directions: Back left corner

name: Sunset West Playground
directions: Behind Ortega Library

name: Lake Anne Brew House
directions: The unisex restrooms are in the back of the room up the stairs to the left when you enter. You have to pass the counter on the way inside.
comment: The place is fairly small, but very liberal- they are major supporters of Pride every year. Pretend you are looking for friends who are already seated if you feel awkward going straight back.

name: Starbucks
directions: In the back on the right, past the coffee bar.  There are two unisex restrooms

name: Paddy's Pub
comment: All 3 bathrooms are single toilet, "gendered" by the main bar but frequently used by anyone. Bathroom in the front is unisex.

name: School of Art
directions: End of the hallway on the right
comment: Open to students only as a Covid-19 precaution.

name: Group Counseling Practice
comment: Sometimes keep door locked, but if it’s open, come on in. There are 2 gender neutral bathrooms.

name: Montebello City Hall
directions: Head straight up the stairs or go around for accessibility issues. Inside of main foyer, turn to your right at the end of the hall and the restrooms will be there on your right hand side.

name: KB Sushi
directions: Near thr main dining room, right of the lobby

name: Chat Noir Books
directions: Restroom is located at the back of the store.
comment: When the store reopens in-store beverage service (closed currently due to Covid) this restroom is available to the public.

name: St George's Road Toilets
comment: Gendered toilets with a single disabled stall that is available to anyone. Changing table is in another separate room.

name: Eastney Point Toilets
comment: There are gendered toilets and then there is a disabled toilet separate from the rest that is available for anyone to use. The changing table is also situated in here.

name: The Bookshelf
comment: Openly supportive of LGBTQ community.

name: Seddon Deadly Sins Cafe
street: 148 Victoria St, Seddon, Maribyrnong, Victoria 3011 Australia
comment: Incredibly LGBT+ friendly.

name: Totem Books
directions: The wall all the way to the right, past the cafe

name: Mathnasium of Surprise
directions: Inside Mathnasium, back of the center on the right.
comment: Open to anyone who is a member of Mathnasium or family of a student at the time of their visit.

name: Family Dollar
directions: On the right in the back of the store.

name: Water Tower Place
directions: third floor near back

name: The Wichita Area Sexual Assault Center
comment: WASAC is a safe space - you can ask to use the bathroom without being a client.

name: Ulta
directions: In the back by the salon area
comment: You’ll have to ask someone at the salon for the key

name: Kohl's
directions: In the back of the store, next to Customer Service, there is a family restroom that is single room, open to all genders.

name: Walmart
directions: There is a family restroom that is single room in the back of the store by the electronic department.

name: Thomas Raddall Provincial Park
street: 100 Core Loop, Port Joli, NS B0T 1S0, Canada

name: Botanique
directions: Halfway the building, a bit before the counter

name: Modern Corp Auto Sales
directions: One mile north of the Edison Mall, across the street from the Fort Myers Golf Course.

name: Modern Corp Auto Sales
directions: One mile north of the Edison Mall, across from the Fort Myers Golf Course.

name: Westbrook Building
directions: When you go in the main doors to Westbrook, take a right and walk down the hall. Take your first left, and there are gender neutral bathrooms in the space next to the couches.
comment: During COVID, the doors may be locked.

name: Cohocton Dollar General
comment: Sometimes locked. Ask cashier for a key. One key to both doors. They will not ask what one you use. And only one key so if you have it no one else can unlock door.

name: Stater Bros Market
directions: Back of store by meat counter
comment: Not always the cleanest

name: Surowiec
directions: Right after you leave the stairs when entering the bar.
comment: The restroom is in the bar, so It's open at late hours and it's for the customers, but the whole place is for and run by LGBT+ people, so if you ask to use the toilet, I'm sure they will be ok with that.

name: Mayo Clinic
comment: Many Mayo Clinic buildings have gender neutral restrooms, but there are also gendered multi-stall in some locations. Ask at the information desk or any check-in desk for the closest gender neutral bathroom. They updated signage over 5 years ago to be more inclusive, as well!

name: Einstein Middle School
directions: Several Around the School, single, non-gendered bathrooms located at all bathroom areas
comment: Must be a student or staff, only open during the school year

name: Misty Bolling
directions: In floral section
comment: Furring store hours

name: Misty Bolling
directions: Back of restaurant
comment: Customer use only

name: Victoria Conference Center
directions: On the second floor. You can go up the stairs or take the elevator. Either way once on the second floor go to the left and through the doorway. It's about ten feet down the hall on the left.

name: Choice Orchards
directions: Straight back and to the left
comment: Choice Orchards is only open seasonally, so make sure they're open when you'd be there! When they are open, their hours are 9-5 seven days a week.

name: Servicios De Ingenieria Castro
street: Republica de Cuba, No Ext 301 NTE, No Interior 4, Cuarto piso Lazaro Cardenas
directions: Cuarto piso.
comment: Entra preguntando por el baño, sin necesitar de comprar o ser cliente del local.

name: Freshii
directions: Single bathroom in the back of the store
comment: You have to be a paying customer so just act like you are or you are a skip the dishes person

name: Baby’s Burgers, Broast and Bar
directions: Gender neutral bathrooms in a very friendly restaurant.

name: East haven beach
directions: Small building at the entrance of the carpark
comment: No disabled/accessible toilet. Only one toilet per gendered entrance, unmanned and locally ran (cleaned and maintained by East haven locals)

name: Dundee Double Shot Coffee
directions: Single restroom
comment: Need to be a paying customer

name: Subway
directions: Far right

name: South suburban sports complex
directions: Upper level by the elevator
comment: This complex is very understanding and accommodating. The restrooms and locker rooms!

name: Overlook Medical Center
directions: Go to front entrance,  make a left part reception and the on on your left down the hall by the elevator

name: Subway
directions: through the front doors and along the right of the store

name: Moran Prairie Library
directions: Through the front turn down the hallway just pas the computers on the right. Through the side door they'll be right in front of you
comment: Only women's restroom has a changing table.

name: Mizpah AMC Hut
directions: Located at the AMC Mizpah Spring Hut. Park at the Crawford Notch trail head in Bretton Woods, NH and follow the Crawford Path for 1.5 miles. Take the Mizpah Cutoff trail for a direct route to the hut and restroom.
comment: An alternate route with amazing views is to take the Crawford Notch trail and summit Mt. Pierce, a NH “4000 Footer” mountain, then follow the Webster trail to the hut and return down via the Mizpah Cutoff trail.

name: The Walnut Avenue Cafe
directions: About halfway into the restaurant on the right side.
comment: You have to be a paying customer. 2 gender neutral private bathrooms.

name: Chambers Purely Boulders
comment: Must be member of the climbing gym

name: Market Basket #42
directions: In Market's Cafe
comment: As long as you are a store patron whether shopping or getting a meal at the café you will be all set.

name: Yorkdale mall
directions: Located near the Pottery Barn

name: Nonprofit Center
directions: All bathrooms in the building are either marked as transgender-friendly or gender neutral, but only the first floor is open to the general public.
comment: First floor is open to the public. If you are attending meetings on any of the other floors, they are all transgender-friendly.  The stall on the 4th floor is gender neutral.

name: The Net Loft on Granville Island
Oak Hills High School (Nurse's Office)
directions: Nurse's office restroom.
comment: Go to the nurse and that restroom is for all genders! Many of my transgendered friends that went there used that restroom!

name: Far Eastern University
directions:
1. Accounts Business and Finance (IABF) Building - 3rd floor
2. Admissions Office - 2nd floor
3. Alfredo Reyes Hall (ARH) - 3rd floor
4. Architecture and Fine Arts (IARFA) Building - 2nd floor
5. Arts Building (AB) - 2nd floor
6. Education Building (EB) - 4th floor
7. Nursing Building (NB) - 3rd floor
8. Nicanor Reyes Hall (NRH) - 2nd floor
9. Science Building (SB) - 3rd floor
comment: Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, schools remain closed as online classes are being implemented in the institution. It is likely that since March 2020, no students were able to use the restroom because of the lockdown and mobility restrictions in Metro Manila.

name: Marketview Arts
comment: The building is open to the public Tuesday-Saturday.

name: York College Center for Community Engagement
comment: Bathrooms available during operating hours (open Monday-Friday 9am-4pm from August to May, Monday-Thursday 9am-4pm and Friday 9am-11am in the summer).

name: Cloud Nine Flotation Center
directions: This business is run in a home so you just go in the front door,  but you need to be a client.
comment: This is a very trans, gender fluid,  intersex etc friendly business. You do need to hand an appointment to float but you will feel very welcome and valued here. The bathroom is really clean,  and also has a shower with all needed bathing products.

name: Geological Sciences -- Basement
directions: If entering from circle drive, take stairs or elevator to basement (press G on elevator). If entering from parking lot behind building, enter through accessible entrance. Restroom is located between rooms 15 and 17, near the elevator.
comment: Single stall restroom with toilet and urinal.

name: Blackmarket Bakery
directions: On the right when you walk in.

name: Brown Dog Cafe
directions: In the back on the left
comment: It's a restaurant, so I think you typically have to be eating there.

name: First Horizon Bank
directions: Guard or employee must let you back
comment: Must be a customer

name: Half Price Books
directions: Straight back the right hand side of the store through the clearance section, hallway with two doors
comment: Do not have to be a paying customer, can come in just to use the restrooms

name: River Valley Co-op
directions: Near the cafe
comment: Always clean.  Each bathroom is private.

name: River Valley Co-op
directions: All bathrooms - near the cafe area.

name: Speedway
directions: Immediate left once you go in the front door.

name: PetCo
directions: In the very back, middle of the store, in the alcove between the tall red shelves.
comment: Two individual unisex bathrooms, at least 15 square feet each, sink and mirror inside. Both have a metal bar by the toilet itself, and the one on the left has a hook on the back of the door. Staff are very nice.
